Our Heritage

A Street of Cultural Convergence

Nestled in the heart of George Town's UNESCO World Heritage core zone, Armenian Street stands as a living testament to Penang's rich multicultural tapestry. Since Ernest Zacharevic's celebrated murals appeared in 2012, this historic street has captured the imagination of travelers worldwide.

Yet with rising popularity comes a challenge: the risk of reducing deep cultural heritage to mere photo opportunities. Our mission is to transform Armenian Street from a fleeting check-in spot into an immersive journey through living history.

"Every brick tells a story, every doorway holds a memory waiting to be discovered."

Interactive Journey

The Stamp Collection Route

Your passport to cultural discovery

We've designed an interactive stamp collection experience that guides visitors through 10 curated checkpoints, revealing hidden stories and cultural treasures. Each stamp represents a piece of cultural memory, weaving together the complete story of Armenian Street.
